text: Helen McEntee (born 8 June 1986) is an Irish Fine Gael politician who has been the Minister for Justice since June 2020. Between April to November 2021 and November 2022 to June 2023, she was a minister without portfolio. She has been a Teachta Dála (TD) for the Meath East constituency since 2013. She also was Minister of State for European Affairs from 2017 to 2020 and Minister of State for Mental Health and Older People from 2016 to 2017. ==References== Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:Members of Fine Gael Category:Government ministers of Ireland Category:Members of Dáil Éireann
